properties.title: Burstinden - Snösäker
properties.description:
From the top of the Burstinden you have a spectacular view down to the Senjahopen and out over the sea. The top trip can really be recommended to make the end of the day when you can enjoy a beautiful sunset. In bad weather there is forest skiing. Of course not in class with Serre Chevalier, but still something to do at poor visibility and snowfall.

**Height** 753 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** There are parts above 30 degrees.

**Length up:** 2.5 kilometers

**Exposition** West and East

**Elevation** 753 meters

**Duration** 2 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Park at qualifying along road 862, about 7 kilometers east of Senjahopen.

**Starting point GPS** 69.474172, 17,550488

## Up

1. Go west, through the forest, up towards the southwest of the Burstinden.

2. When you get to the pass, walk around the lake along the north side.

3. Continued then in a northwesterly direction for a few hundred meters until you reach a flatter lot.

4. Now you turn off the northeast and go up to the top.

## Down

The same way down as up.

## Dangers

The hanging drives on top. Avalanches on the top part (from the top down to the lake) that are over 30 degrees.

**Map**

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

properties.title: Husfjellet - Snösäker
properties.description:
Husfjellet is a quick top trip with fantastic views of the Ersfjord and the open sea. A perfect top to enjoy the sunset across the Atlantic.

**Height** 632 Möh

**Difficulty** easy

**Slope** below 30 degrees.

**Length** 2.5 km

**Exposition** South/southwest

**Elevation** 630 height meters

**Duration (up)** 1-2 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** From Bergsbotn you continue road 862 in a western direction until the road goes to road 251. Continue on the west and park along the road in Stamnesvika, about 2 km after Skaland.

**Starting point** 69.453472, 17.264285

## Up

1. Go in a northeastern direction from the car. Aim for the Litjebrus.

2. When you get over the tree line, you turn off the northwest and continue along the comb to the top.

## Down

The same way down as up.

## Dangers

It is steep along the east side of the top. Watch out if there are suspension drives.

**Map**

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

properties.title: Keipen - Snösäker
properties.description:
The view from the top of Keipen is extremely beautiful where fjord meets mountains and sea. This is a spectacular tour that is a must on a visit to Norway's second largest island. The Keipen is considered by many to be Senja's abo best top trip.

**Height** 938 Möh

**Difficulty**: Medium

**Slope** below 30 degrees except for a passage before the top exceeding 30 degrees.

**Length** 3 km

**Exposition** Syd

**Elevation** 840 height meters

**Duration** 2 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Park at Mefjordvatnan. Here it is about 17 kilometers from the Senjahopen and here is a parking pocket for 4-5 cars, along the south side of the road.

**Starting point GPS** 69.475577, 17.734337

## Up

1. Through the forest and hold west as the trees are sparse out.

2. Up on the plate you go either north or slightly west to take heed directly.

3. Then aim at the bottom and lowest part of the top comb. Watch out for this snow field exceeding 30 degrees.

4. Once up on the comb, just knead up to the top.

Down

1. Same road as up.

2. The gutter that you see on the western part of the mountain. It is clearly visible when you walk up.

## Dangers

The snow field before the top part exceeds 30 degrees.

## Map

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

properties.title: Kvaenan - Snösäker
properties.description:
Kvaenan is a bit remote compared to the more popular ski trips at Senja. But the mountain is well worth a visit. From the top you can either go down the same way you went up, or put turns down for the steeper and spectacular southwest side. This top trip describes the east top and then ride down on the north side. Since it is just a north side, this is a top trip that often works late into the season.

**Height** 967 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** There are parts steeper than 30 degrees

**Length** 4 kilometers

**Exposition** Nord

**Elevation** 930 meters

**Duration** 3 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** When you arrive from the north along Route 243 you park on the left side of the road between Indre and Surface Kvaenanbukta.

**Starting point GPS** 69.228041, 17.128029

## Up

1. Go in a southerly direction through the forest.

2. Above the tree line you aim at the small top 556.

3. Go around it and then continue towards the eastern top in a southeastern direction.

## Down

1. Same road as up

2. Down on the southwest side. This part is steeper and ends at road 243, about 6 kilometers from the car. Either you shark back (there is traffic on the road) or you go back. But then you have to get through a car/truck tunnel of about 1 kilometer.

## Dangers

There are parts steeper than 30 degrees, but you can avoid some of these fields.

**Map**

properties.title: Litjemoa - Snösäker
properties.description:
Litjemoa is a really good trip for the beginner. Please incline, nice skiing and wonderful views from the top over fjords and out towards the open sea.

**Height** 839 Möh.

**Difficulty** easy

**Starting point** Park at the Krokelvatnet at 300 meters above sea level, just after the tunnel along road 862 if you come from the north.

**Starting point GPS** 69.397354, 17,49238

## Up

1. Directly at the parking lot you take into account in the small valley to the northeast.

2. At about 450 height meters you turn west and go towards the top.

3. Make a U-turn 100 height meters below the top and go east the last bit. On hard ground, 2-3 strokes may be done before you reach the top.

properties.title: Lutnespurka - Snösäker
properties.description:
Lutnes Purka offers perhaps Senja's most interesting and best forest skiing. Svisha past trees in good slope while the fjord is below you.

**Height** About 500 meters

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** There are parts steeper than 30 degrees

**Length** 2 kilometers

**Exposition** South and East

**Elevation** 500 meters

**Duration** 1 - 1.5 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Drive road 862 to Bergsbotn. Drive another 1 kilometer west to Indregård and park on the right side of the road, at a worn and old red house.

**Starting point GPS** 69.441525, 17.4544

1. Go straight north from the red and worn house.

2. Follow the treeless street until it gets flat.

3. Fold off to the west and take you up through forest.

4. Above the tree line you turn off towards the north and move on to the top.

## Down

The same way down as up.

## Dangers

Steep passages in the forest. The northern parts of the forest are steeper than the closest comb.

**Map**

properties.title: Luttinden - Snösäker
properties.description:
Luttinden offers most things. Large riding surfaces, a cool top comb and, as usual, the Norwegian view with fjord and mountains. Here you get many high quality turns. The ride ends in a relatively narrow forest, which, despite this, does not remove the enjoyment of this top trip.

**Height** 652 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** A short traverse with snowfields over you that is above 30 degrees.

**Length** 2 km

**Exposition** southwest/southeast

**Elevation** 650 height meters

**Duration** 2 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Drive road 862 to Bergsbotn. Drive another 1 kilometer west and park near Gammelgården.

**Starting point** 69.438651, 17.40675

## Up

1. Go in a northwesterly direction and tangle you through the stringent forest.

2. Continued in the same direction above the tree line.

3. At about 500 meters height you turn off west and take you up to the comb. Here you cross a steep snow field.

4. On the comb, you turn off northeast and continue along the comb to the top.

## Down

The same way down as up.

## Dangers

Steep parts over you all the way up to the comb.

**Map**

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

properties.title: Luttindsrenna - Snösäker
properties.description:
Luttindrenna is a spectacular gutter that you see from many peaks on Senja. It is large, wide and relatively steep. A fun ride with both good views and exciting skiing.

**Height** 730 Möh

**Difficulty** difficult

**Slope** above 30 degrees

**Length** 4 kilometers

**Exposition** Southeast

**Elevation** 740 meters, of which the gutter is 300 meters

**Duration (up)** 3 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Park in Bergsbotn along Route 862, about 19 kilometers south of Senjahopen.

**Starting point GPS** 69.46451, 17.346296

## Up

1. Follow the marked path in a northerly direction to the Lutvatnet.

2. Then fold off in a northwesterly direction and follow Lutdalen all the way to the gutter. It is clearly visible throughout the march.

3. Up in the gutter.

A more direct road up is northeast from Steinfjord up to the start of the gutter. It is a faster trip, but then you should keep track of the snow conditions in the gutter before you go it. Or you go straight east from Steinfjord and then go up in the gutter.

## Down

The same way down as up.

## Dangers

In the case of hard ground, the gliding risk is in case great. Snow release from the side cliffs.

## Map

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

properties.title: Skolpan - Snösäker
properties.description:
The schoolpan has the same starting point as the more famous peaks Lillmoa and Stormoa. The ride down offers both large open fields and sparse forest skiing. And everything with a fjord view of course.

**Height** 779 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** There are parts steeper than 30 degrees

**Elevation** 579 meters

**Duration (up)** 1.5 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Drive road 862 south from Bergsbotn. After the tunnel you continue about 1 kilometer and park in a meeting pocket along the northern side of the road.

**Starting point GPS** 69.395662, 17.464571

1. You see the top from the road and just go straight north from the car.

2. At the top back, take off the northwest so you continue to take the top to the top.

3. In hard ground it can be nice to leave the skis at the back and walk with boots and spells to the top.

## Down

Straight south, over the open fields, through the forest and down to the road.

## Dangers

Hanging drives on top. There are steeper parts than 30 degrees, but you can avoid some of these.

**Map**

properties.title: Snaufjellet - Snösäker
properties.description:
This is a nice top trip where you are rewarded with a senselessly beautiful view from the top part of the mountain. On the way up you will also see the awesome Luttindennan.

**Height** 755 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** below 30 degrees except for a passage in the middle of the tour.

**Exposition** Syd

**Elevation** 755 meters

**Duration** 2-3 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** Park in Bergsbotn along Route 862, about 19 kilometers south of Senjahopen.

**Starting point GPS** 69.441495, 17.421827

## Up

1. Follow the marked path in a northerly direction towards Lutvatnet.

2. Towards the end of Lutvatnet, you turn off to the east.

3. Go up for the slope and when it flicks off to the north.

4. Then follow the northwest direction towards the top.

The same way down as up.

properties.title: Store hesten - Snösäker
properties.description:
The big horse is a real Senja classic. Here you take into account directly from the car and the normal road is both simple and relatively safe. But for those who want challenges, the top offers steeper skiing in the form of fine gutters.

**Height** 874 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** Forest parties above 30 degrees.

**Length** 4 km

**Exposition** West and northeast

**Elevation** 870 height meters

**Duration (up)** 3 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** from Mefjordvaer, drive 862 east towards Mefjordbotn. Park between the second and third tunnel, between Svarthola and qualifying.

**Starting point** 69.461694, 17.580786

## Up

1. From the parking lot you walk in a southwest direction, up through the pot, towards the pass between the big horse and the Litlehesten.

2. Follow the eastern edge of the little Hestvatnet until you have the west side of the Great Hest above you.

3. Continue in a southeastern direction along the back in the direction of Storfjellet's peak and then further east to the saddle between the big horse and Storfjellet.

4. Fold off to the north and walk your back up to the top.

## Down

The same way down as up.

## Dangers

Parts of the forest are above 30 degrees.

**Map**

properties.title: Svanfjellet, via västra sidan - Snösäker
properties.description:
# Svanfjellet, via västra sidan - Snösäker

Svanefjellet's west side offers steeper skiing compared to the west side. Here, too, it is about large open spaces and sparse forest, but in a steeper format. The easiest way is to go to the top via the east side, and then go down the west. The ride ends with an approximately 600 meter walk to the car.

**Height** 791 Möh

**Difficulty** means

**Slope** The Forest Party exceeds 30 degrees.

**Length** 2.5 km

**Exposition** Southwest

**Elevation** 580 height meters

**Duration** 2 hours

**Glacier** No.

**Starting point** From the Run Run 86 in a western direction, towards Gryllefjord. After about 10 kilometers you turn left, towards Sifjord. Three kilometers later, the road turns off to the north and you enter Kaperdalen. Drive past the two seashers to you and park along the western side at the end of the other lake.

**Starting point** 69.285678, 17.365179

## Up

1. Go through the forest in a northeastern direction and take a view east of the mountain 504 towards the third peak.

2. At about 450 meters height you come to a flatter party. Continue on the back between the lake in the northwest and a sinking in the southeast.

3. Take aim at the pass between the third peak and Svanfjellet.

4. At the pass you take off southeast and continue to the top.

Down

From the top you keep a southern direction, past a back and down into a pot -like formation. Continue in the pot and through the forest down to the road, all in a southwest direction.

## Dangers

Parties exceeding 30 degrees in the forest area.

**Map**

properties.title: Tebbeltuva, Combe Sud
properties.description:
**Height** 788 moh

**Orientation** SE

**Ascent difficulty** AD-

**Skiing difficulty** 2.2 E3

**Gradient** <25° then >30/35°



## Start

 Merfjordvaer (0 m) - Bratthesten Tunnel, a 20-minute drive from the village of Merfjordvaer in Mefjorden Bay



## Route

 From the village of Merfjordvaer, ascend the wide southern valley following the small, semi-private cross-country ski trail laid out by the owner of the village lodges. Cross the birch trees to tackle the valley furthest down the valley. Around 550 m, the slope steepens sharply and heads to the right of the large rocky outcrop in the area (unfortunately not clearly marked on the map). Take this arc-shaped valley from right to left to finish the ascent at a 30/35° angle. Stop on a small promontory 30m from the summit (you can finish on foot on rock and with a bit of gas... bring a rope just in case). Descend in the same way, with the option of searching for a long gorge at the end to your left, around 400m.

It's possible to leave Mefjordvaer harbor via the North Valley. Easier, with a steep couloir at the summit.



## Equipment

Rope for the summit
